        <h3>The Multi-Stage Logic: Decoding NTA Selection Lists</h3>
        <p>A frequent search regarding **nta recruitment marks 2024** is about the 'Selection Threshold'. For the 2024 cycle, NTA follows a strict national-policy threshold:</p>
        <ul style="margin-left: 20px;">
            <li><strong>Tier-I CBT (Common)</strong>: The first computer-based test testing GA, Reasoning, Math, and Language. Marks are normalized if held in multiple shifts.</li>
            <li><strong>Tier-II Skill Test</strong>: Qualified candidates appear for Typing (30-35 wpm) or specialized technical tests for professional roles.</li>
            <li><strong>The Final Merit</strong>: Calculated based on the aggregate Tier-I marks (provided the candidate qualifies for Tier-II and Tier-III if applicable).</li>
        <li><strong>Outcome</strong>: This ensures that central institutions are staffed with academics and administrators who are both technically and mentally proficient.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>How to Check NTA (Institutional Recruitment) Result 2024 officially?</h3>
        <p>While the informational sites are for news, the **NTA Official Link** is for selection. To check officially:</p>
        <p>
            1. Visit the **official NTA recruitment portal** (recruitment.nta.nic.in).<br>
            2. Choose your specific institutional recruitment link (e.g., DU Rec or IGNOU Rec).<br>
            3. Click on the 'Score Card' or 'Selection List' link on the dashboard.<br>
            4. Enter your **Application Number** (as on the admit card) and **Date of Birth**.<br>
            5. Enter the **Security Pin** (Captcha) and click on 'Login'.<br>
            6. View your 'Detailed Scorecard' showing Sectional and Normalized total marks.<br>
            7. For the Merit List, download the PDF containing the roll numbers of selected candidates.<br>
            8. Verification: Check the 'Status of Qualification' for the next stage (Skill Test/DV).
        </p>

